Under such circumstances as these, if the claim ol the praetorian successor is overridden by that ol the heres, the bonorum possessio is said to be sine re, or ineffectual: ‘bonorum possessio aut cum re datur, aut sine re: curn re, si is qui accepit cum effectu bona re· tinent: sinere, cum alius iure civili evincere hereditatem possit’ Ulpian, reg. 28. 13 : cf. Gaius iii. 3 5-38.
